         <abstract>
            <p>A detailed review of the pension related provisions of OBRA are provided and their effects on annual funding requirements are examined. The analysis demonstrates that OBRA has increased the volatility of year-to-year pension contributions and in so doing has decreased the capacity of a defined benefit pension plan to serve as a risk-offsetting device. Two primary implications for corporate pension policy are identified and available empirical evidence provides tentative support for these conclusions.</p>
         </abstract>
